					</div>

					<div class="comment-text">
						<p>This is interesting as I made soupe a l&#8217;oignon two nights ago and was thinking along the same lines. It fascinates me that a peasant dish has taken on such luxury connotations in modern times. </p>
<p>But I&#8217;m not really sure I agree with the contention that a beef stock made with roasted marrow bones and old mirepoix vegetables really detracts from the economy of this dish. Real AOC gruyere is a luxury at $40+/kg, certainly not beef stock. I think they&#8217;re both worth springing for if you want to do it right.</p>
					</div>

